      "acceptanceCriteria": "Solver must be validated against standard benchmark cases; version control and change documentation required.",
      "rationale": "ANSYS Fluent 2022R2 was used under a documented quality management system. Version control records and release notes confirm solver integrity. Benchmark comparisons against FDA-published pipe flow and backward-facing step cases demonstrate numerical correctness at the required gradation level."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical code verification",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Solver must pass at least one method of manufactured solutions or equivalent benchmark verification test relevant to the physics modeled.",
      "rationale": "The incompressible Navier-Stokes solver was verified against the Taylor-Green vortex manufactured solution and the lid-driven cavity benchmark at Re=1000. Convergence rates were consistent with second-order spatial accuracy. No code defects were identified that affect the hemolysis prediction application."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Grid convergence index (GCI) below 5% for primary QoIs at the selected production mesh resolution.",
      "rationale": "Richardson extrapolation across four mesh refinement levels confirmed GCI values below 2% for hemolysis index and below 3.5% for peak shear stress at all five COU operating points. The fine mesh (8.1M cells) was selected for production runs based on the balance of accuracy and computational cost established in the convergence analysis."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental test conditions must be documented with sufficient fidelity to enable computational replication within stated uncertainty bounds.",
      "rationale": "In vitro test conditions from the Morrison et al. dataset are fully documented including fluid properties (bovine blood, hematocrit 35±2%), temperature (37°C), flow rates (2–6 L/min), and rotational speeds (2000–3500 RPM). Boundary conditions in the CFD model were set to match measured inlet velocity profiles and outlet pressure conditions within reported measurement uncertainty."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative comparison metrics (e.g., RMSE, mean absolute error) must be reported for all primary QoIs against experimental reference data.",
      "rationale": "Hemolysis index predictions were compared against experimental measurements using mean absolute error (MAE = 0.08 RH units) and normalized RMSE (nRMSE = 9.3%). Wall shear stress comparisons yielded agreement within 15% at 92% of measurement locations. All metrics satisfy the MRL 2 acceptance thresholds defined in the assessment plan."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs must be directly linked to the clinical decision criterion (RH < 1) and the intended use of the model.",
      "rationale": "The primary QoI is the relative hemolysis index (RH), which is directly specified in the COU acceptance criterion. Secondary QoIs (scalar shear stress, exposure time distributions) are mechanistically linked to the Power Law hemolysis model used in the simulation. The QoI selection is fully consistent with FDA guidance on hemolysis prediction for blood-contacting devices."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
