      "rationale": "Validation experiments used the same FDA generic centrifugal blood pump geometry as the COU model. Operating conditions span the COU envelope (2–6 L/min, 2000–3500 RPM). Bovine blood at physiological hematocrit was used as the test fluid, consistent with accepted hemolysis testing standards. The validation scenario is judged sufficiently representative of the COU to support MRL 2 credibility conclusions."
